<br>
1. look at druids for a few months and make them even more powerful than they already are. Yep, you guessed it, increase that tracking skill even more so that bards are now below them in that area. Give them a bunch of heals, hmm maybe a new dmg shield. Wait, i know, how about giving the druids the graveyard shift in Skyfire and we can get their nice safe orb? Can't be outdone can they. Hell, druids need all the help they can get anyway.<br>
<br>
2. Definitely need to give those mages ports. Wait, i have it, remove ports from wizards and give them to mages. Even better, give a mage translocate as well. A mage is so close to our dmg no-one will tell the difference anyway. Then wizards wont be needed for porting all those mages around to get their groups.<br>
<br>
3. Wizards are okay, wonder why they are complaining? they only med for 15 minutes between mobs at level 59 and do next to no dmg against those velius uber mobs. cant have them doing too much dmg, would make the druid look bad with their free armour dots, long snare and mana regen form of the howler. Cant have a necro killing any less than 3 mobs to the wizard's one can we.<br>
<br>
4. I wouldnt mind more dmg output for less mana, but come one - 10 fizzles in a row with a max alteration skill on Atol's is embarasing! I think the mobs would die from laughter before our DDs connect, not to mention having the endless taunting from fellow group members on the bets they have taken on the number of fizzles we will get on the next pull.<br>
<br>
5. Is it me, or have wizards been grabbing their ankles from minute one?<br>
<br>
Yours,<br>
<br>
Mildly concerned wizard,<br>
<br>
Sarx<br>
59 Evoker<br>
